Muhammad Barkindo, the late secretary-general of the Organisation of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC), met with President Muhammadu Buhari on Tuesday at the State House in Abuja hours before his death. Among those present at the meeting were Timipre Sylva, minister of state petroleum resources; Ibrahim Gambari, chief of staff; Mele Kyari, group managing director of the Nigerian National Petroleum Company (NNPC); Farouk Ahmed, CEO of board of Nigerian Midstream and Downstream Petroleum Regulatory Authority (NPRA), and Suraj Matori, PR and information OPEC. Barkindo had also delivered a speech to oil and gas stakeholders at the ongoing 2022 Nigerian oil and gas conference and exhibition in Abuja. His demise was announced by Kyari, GMD of NNPC in the early hours of Wednesday. Below are photos of him with Buhari. PRESIDENT BUHARI AUDIENCE WITH OUTGOING OPEC SEC GEN BAKINDO L-R; President Muhammadu Buhari, Minister of State Petroleum Resources, Mr Timipre Sylva and the outgoing OPEC Sec Gen Mr. Mohammed Barkindo accompanied by his Children, Abubakar, Yahaya Barkindo during an audience with the Outgoing Secretary General of Organisation of the Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC), Mr Barkindo at the State House Ab uja., PHOTO; SUNDAY AGHAEZE. JULY 5TH 2022 PRESIDENT BUHARI AUDIENCE WITH OUTGOING OPEC SEC GEN BAKINDO 7A&BB L-R; Minister of State Petroleum Resources, Mr Timipre Sylva, Chief of Staff Prof Ibrahim Gambari, President Muhammadu Buhari, the outgoing OPEC Sec Gen Mr. Mohammed Barkindo with his Children and others during an audience with the Outgoing Secretary General of Organisation of the Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC), Mr Barkindo at the State House Ab uja., PHOTO; SUNDAY AGHAEZE. JULY 5TH 2022 PRESIDENT BUHARI AUDIENCE WITH OUTGOING OPEC SEC GEN BAKINDO 7A&BB L-R; Minister of State Petroleum Resources, Mr Timipre Sylva, Chief of Staff Prof Ibrahim Gambari, President Muhammadu Buhari, the outgoing OPEC Sec Gen Mr. Mohammed Barkindo with his Children a